 AI Security and Governance

 Short Description
AI Security and Governance explores the principles, risks, and safeguards needed to responsibly design, deploy, and manage AI systems. It emphasizes trust, transparency, compliance, and ethical practices, preparing learners to address challenges in modern AI-driven environments.

Long Description
AI Security and Governance is a comprehensive course that examines how artificial intelligence can be developed and deployed responsibly. It covers risk management, transparency, compliance with global standards, and ethical considerations that ensure AI systems remain trustworthy and secure. In today’s world, AI influences nearly every aspect of life—from healthcare and finance to education and entertainment—making governance essential to prevent misuse and build public trust. For me, learning this course has been transformative: it has deepened my understanding of how AI shapes society, highlighted the importance of protecting data and ensuring fairness, and inspired me to think critically about how I can contribute to building safe, ethical, and impactful AI solutions.

---

  Key Topics
- Risk management in AI systems  
- Transparency and explainability  
- Compliance with global standards  
- Ethical and responsible AI practices  

 Why It Matters
AI is reshaping industries and daily life. Understanding governance ensures that innovation remains safe, fair, and trustworthy.
